<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-13956] FileDataSet does not support a single file larger than 1024 bytes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-13956</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Using dataset with a FileDataSet configured with a single file - new FileDataSet(filename) - doesn&apos;t work as expected if the file is more than 1024 bytes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Expected result: The whole file is used as the dataset source.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Actual result: The file gets split into multiple messages at 1024 byte boundaries.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
